{"id":32974,"date":"2019-07-30T11:54:14","date_gmt":"2019-07-30T07:54:14","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=32974"},"modified":"2019-07-30T11:54:14","modified_gmt":"2019-07-30T07:54:14","slug":"prophet-recognizes-his-ummah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/prophet-recognizes-his-ummah\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Hereafter: The Prophet recognizes his Ummah on Judgment Day"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Darda reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>I will be the first to be called to prostrate on the Day of Resurrection. I will be the first to be called to raise his head and I will look in front of me. I will recognize my nation among the nations, from behind me, to my right and to my left.<\/strong>\u201d A man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, how will you recognize your nation among the nations from Noah until now?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>They will have radiant streaks from the traces of ablution. No one will have that but them. I will recognize them when they are given their records in their right hands, and I will recognize them as their descendants run before them.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 21623<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih li ghayrihi<\/em><\/strong> (authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0651\u064e\u0631\u0652\u062f\u064e\u0627\u0621\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e <strong>\u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0648\u0651\u064e\u0644\u064f \u0645\u064e\u064